##HOTEL COLLAPSE MOMENT EXPOSURE! The national medical team went to the area

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

This is a roundup for the paper

On the night of March 7,2020, a hotel in Licheng district, Quanzhou City, Fujian Province, collapsed. About 70 people are trapped. In the early morning hours of August 8, Quanzhou Radio and television broadcast footage of the moment of collapse.

Editor, Zhang Zhaoyi, source, Quanzhou Radio and television station, People's Daily Editor in charge: Jiang Gewei

As of 8:16 a.m. , 48 people had been rescued, according to the People's Daily. Previously reported on "Emergency Management Department: Serious Accountability under the law. "

The National Health Commission attached great importance to this issue and promptly dispatched two groups of 18 national-level medical and health emergency expert teams to support local health emergency response work, including the treatment of the wounded.

The first group of experts was dispatched from Fuzhou and Xiamen on the evening of the 7th, it is composed of 14 specialists from the Fujian Medical University, the First Affiliated Hospital and the Xiamen University, specializing in critical care medicine, trauma orthopedics, psychological intervention, hospital sense prevention and control, etc. .

The second group of experts set off from Guangzhou early on the 8th, composed of 4 experts from the First Affiliated Hospital of the National Sun Yat-sen University in the specialties of critical care medicine, neurosurgery, traumatology and orthopaedics, and thoracic surgery.

After the accident, the local health department launched the first emergency response, rapid transfer of the injured and medical treatment and other work. Leading a team of provincial experts, he arrived in Quanzhou overnight to direct and coordinate the rescue and treatment of the injured.

Currently, the injured are being treated in four hospitals in Quanzhou. National, provincial and municipal experts formed a joint medical expert group to assess the wounded one by one, implement a one-person-one-policy, closely monitor the changes in the condition of the injured, dynamically adjust and improve the treatment plan, and spare no effort in treating the injured, meanwhile, the prevention and control of infectious diseases among medical staff and hospital infection should be done strictly.

(integrated from wechat public number "healthy China" , People's Daily, Quanzhou Radio and television station)
